==Ancient Greek==

===Etymology===
A primary particle; 

===Pronunciation===
*ἀπό / apo / apo'

===Particle===
'''ἀπό'''

# “[[off]]”, that is, [[away]] (from something near), in various senses (of place, time, or relation; literally or figuratively): - (X here-) after, ago, at, because of, before, by (the space of), for (-th), [[from]], in, ([[out]]) of, off, (up-) on (-ce), since, with. 
*In composition (as a prefix) it usually denotes separation, departure, cessation, completion, reversal, etc.

